bib.title: Fragmentation Cross Sections Of Medium-Energy 35Cl,40Ar And 48Ti Beams On Elemental Targets

free_txt: Three pairs of position sensitive Si(Li)
detectors with depth/active radius of 3mm/1.1cm,
5mm/1.9cm and 0.85-1.0mm/2cm were used. Position
data were not used.
Systematic uncertainties dominate the total.
Statistical uncertainties are negligible.
Sources of systematic uncertainties include
-lack of precision in determination particle energy
at point of interaction
-placement of cuts in data analysis
-losses due to nuclear interaction in the detector
-limited precision in target density
Each of these sources were estimated on the order of
1%. Additional uncertainty are due to variation of
beam parameters, typicaly around 5%.
Samples with natural composition were used.
Target depth (thickness) varied between 2.7 and 43%
of interaction length  typical values were
between 5 and 15% of interaction length.
C   - 4g/cm**2
Al  - 2g/cm**2
